
@startuml
' Class Diagram for De Lijn's MENSO Season Ticket System

class Bus {
  -id: String
  -line: Line
  -currentTrajectory: Trajectory
}

class Line {
  -lineNumber: Integer
  -name: String
  -category: Category
  -trajectories: Set<Trajectory>
}

class Trajectory {
  -id: String
  -description: String
  -status: Status (approved, pending, suspended, cancelled)
  -approvalHistory: List<ApprovalRequest>
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

class ApprovalRequest {
  -id: String
  -trajectory: Trajectory
  -requestDate: Date
  -status: Status (pending, approved, rejected, revised)
  -revisions: List<Revision>
}

class Revision {
  -id: String
  -approvalRequest: ApprovalRequest
  -date: Date
  -changes: String
}

class Category {
  -id: Integer
  -name: String
  -priceFactor: Double
}

class MensoUser {
  -userId: String
  -fullName: String
  -homeAddress: String
  -workAddress: String
  -workingHours: String
  -cards: Set<MensoCard>
}

class MensoCard {
  -cardId: String
  -user: MensoUser
  -trips: List<Trip>
}

class Trip {
  -tripId: String
  -date: Date
  -time: Time
  -line: Line
  -bus: Bus
}

class Invoice {
  -invoiceId: String
  -userId: String
  -month: Month
  -totalAmount: Double
  -discount: Double
  -paymentStatus: PaymentStatus
  -trips: List<Trip>
}

class Payment {
  -paymentId: String
  -invoice: Invoice
  -amount: Double
  -date: Date
}

enum Status {
  approved
  pending
  suspended
  cancelled
  rejected
  revised
}

enum PaymentStatus {
  unpaid
  paid
  overdue
}

' Relationships
Bus --> Line
Line --> Trajectory
Trajectory --> ApprovalRequest
ApprovalRequest --> Revision
Line --> Category
MensoUser --> MensoCard
MensoCard --> Trip
Trip --> Line
Trip --> Bus
MensoUser --> Invoice
Invoice --> Trip
Invoice --> Payment
@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Bus`**: Represents each vehicle operated by De Lijn. It has a line and is assigned to a trajectory.
- **`Line`**: A group of overlapping trajectories that form a route. Each line has a category which affects pricing.
- **`Trajectory`**: A specific path or route with approval status and history.
- **`ApprovalRequest` / `Revision`**: Handles the process of getting town authority approval for a trajectory.
- **`Category`**: Determines the price factor for trips taken on lines in that category.
- **`MensoUser`**: A user who subscribes to the MENSO card. Contains personal data used for analysis.
- **`MensoCard`**: Used to register trips automatically when entering the bus.
- **`Trip`**: Records of a trip made using a MENSO card, including date, time, and line.
- **`Invoice` / `Payment`**: Monthly billing system. Invoices are generated from trips and can be paid in any order.

